Coerce objects of class "tt_lst" to "data.frame" and "tbl" (tibble).

Source: R/as_tibble.R
as_tibble.tt_lst.Rd

This method creates a dataframe from the output of tt_test() (which is a list of class "tt_lst").

# S3 method for tt_lst
as_tibble(x, ...)

# S3 method for tt_lst
as.data.frame(x, ...)

Arguments

x

An object of class tt_lst.
...

Not used.

Value

A dataframe.

See also

as_tibble().

Other habitat functions: fgeo_habitat, fgeo_topography, tt_test

Other methods for common generics: as_tibble.demography_ctfs, summary.tt_df

Examples

census <- fgeo.x::tree6_3species
habitat <- fgeo.x::habitat

as_tibble(
  tt_test(census, habitat)
)
